column11: Who would've ever thought that the guy who was just working for a pizza-hut branch would actually end up buying the damn branch?
column13: Who would've ever thought that the guy who was just working for a pizza-hut branch would actually end up buying the damn branch? Nobody, nobody would ever believe it until they'd see it. But that's exactly what happened to me. Unlike most people, I didn't actually have an issue of """"working hard."""" I could see the difference immediately between myself and my other workmates. I did everything I could to learn more, earn more, and have more. From 2012 - 2017, I was working 120-170hrs a week. Anything below that didn't feel like work to me at all. Now I know that this isn't your """"take it easy"""" advice, but I had a dream - and I knew that I had to work hard for it. SO I WORKED HARD. If you want live a life of """"safety"""" but without freedom - then remain in a Fvcking Job. But if you want to live life to the fullest, then COMMIT TO GROWTH. You'll have to take risks... You'll have to take painful punches from life... You'll have to make sacrifices... And you'll have to be consistent. Do this, and you'll live a life less than 1% of people will get to experience. #investments #moneymotivation  #multimillionaire  #cashflow  #entrepreneurship  #business  #entrepreneurlife  #businessowner  #financialfreedom  #india  #indianbusinessowner  #businessmindset  #fypã‚· #foryoupage
